#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:4
msgid "fish_key_reader - explore what characters keyboard keys send"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:9
msgid "fish_key_reader [OPTIONS]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr "描述"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:16
msgid ""
":program:`fish_key_reader` is used to explain how you would bind a certain "
"key sequence. By default, it prints the :doc:`bind <bind>` command for one "
"key sequence read interactively over standard input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:18
msgid ""
"If the character sequence matches a special key name (see ``bind --key-"
"names``),  both ``bind CHARS ...`` and ``bind -k KEYNAME ...`` usage will be "
"shown. In verbose mode (enabled by passing ``--verbose``), additional "
"details about the characters received, such as the delay between chars, are "
"written to standard error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:20
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:22
msgid "**-c** or **--continuous**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:23
msgid ""
"Begins a session where multiple key sequences can be inspected. By default "
"the program exits after capturing a single key sequence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:25
msgid "**-V** or **--verbose**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:26
msgid ""
"Tells fish_key_reader to output timing information and explain the sequence "
"in more detail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:28
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:29
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr "顯示此指令的幫助資訊。"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:31
msgid "**-v** or **--version**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:32
msgid "Displays the current :program:`fish` version and then exits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:35
msgid "Usage Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:37
msgid ""
"In verbose mode, the delay in milliseconds since the previous character was "
"received is included in the diagnostic information written to standard "
"error. This information may be useful to determine the optimal "
"``fish_escape_delay_ms`` setting or learn the amount of lag introduced by "
"tools like ``ssh``, ``mosh`` or ``tmux``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:39
msgid ""
"``fish_key_reader`` intentionally disables handling of many signals. To "
"terminate ``fish_key_reader`` in ``--continuous`` mode do:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:41
msgid "press :kbd:`Control`\\ +\\ :kbd:`C` twice, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:42
msgid "press :kbd:`Control`\\ +\\ :kbd:`D` twice, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:43
msgid "type ``exit``, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:44
msgid "type ``quit``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:47
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_key_reader.rst:51
msgid ""
"> fish_key_reader\n"
"Press a key:\n"
"# press up-arrow\n"
"bind \\e\\[A 'do something'\n"
"\n"
"> fish_key_reader --verbose\n"
"Press a key:\n"
"# press alt+enter\n"
"           hex:   1B  char: \\e\n"
"(  0.027 ms)  hex:    D  char: \\cM  (or \\r)\n"
"bind \\e\\r 'do something'"
msgstr ""
